modules.description: Provides functions to retrieve and manipulate a monotonic time value, including getting the current time, calculating durations, and converting time units. It operates with a custom time type that represents elapsed time since an arbitrary start point. Used in network stack implementations to track timeouts and ensure consistent time progression across different platforms.

Provides functions to measure elapsed nanoseconds and retrieve the clock's period in nanoseconds. Operates on time values derived from a monotonic clock source. Used for precise timing in performance analysis and event scheduling.

Provides functions to manage and advance a simulated time source, including retrieving the current time, advancing time by a fixed increment, and advancing time by a specified duration. Operates with an internal `int64` reference representing the current time. Used to simulate time progression in network protocols or event-driven systems where real-time is not available.
